verbose_text: L-selectin did not regulate the subsequent differentiation of effector CD8 + T cells either, since the fraction of proliferating cells and the expression of CD44 and other homing associated molecules, intracellular cytokines, and granzymes were similar in L-selectin-sufficient and L-selectin-deficient T cells harvested at days 5 and 8 from virus infected tissues, draining LN, and the spleen.
